  "text": "## FxVanillaOption Type Family Lineage Trace\n\n### Domain Layer (modules/product)\nThe core Joda-Beans domain classes for FX vanilla options form a two-level hierarchy:\n\n1. **FxVanillaOption** (modules/product/src/main/java/com/opengamma/strata/product/fxopt/FxVanillaOption.java) - The un-resolved domain model implementing `FxOptionProduct` and `Resolvable<ResolvedFxVanillaOption>`. This is a Joda-Beans immutable class marked with `@BeanDefinition` that represents a vanilla FX option with properties including the underlying FX single leg, long/short direction, expiry time, and expiry zone.\n\n2. **FxVanillaOptionTrade** (modules/product/src/main/java/com/opengamma/strata/product/fxopt/FxVanillaOptionTrade.java) - A trade wrapper around `FxVanillaOption`, implementing `FxOptionTrade` and `ResolvableTrade<ResolvedFxVanillaOptionTrade>`. It adds trade-level metadata (TradeInfo) and premium information.\n\n3. **ResolvedFxVanillaOption** (modules/product/src/main/java/com/opengamma/strata/product/fxopt/ResolvedFxVanillaOption.java) - The resolved form of `FxVanillaOption`, implementing `ResolvedProduct`. This class contains fully resolved data with concrete dates and rates (no adjustments or reference data lookups required).\n\n4. **ResolvedFxVanillaOptionTrade** (modules/product/src/main/java/com/opengamma/strata/product/fxopt/ResolvedFxVanillaOptionTrade.java) - The resolved form of `FxVanillaOptionTrade`, containing a `ResolvedFxVanillaOption` as its product field.\n\n### Pricing Layer (modules/pricer)\nThe FxVanillaOption supports two pricing methods: Black (lognormal model) and Vanna-Volga (for smile effects). Each method has a product-level and trade-level pricer:\n\n1. **BlackFxVanillaOptionProductPricer** (modules/pricer/src/main/java/com/opengamma/strata/pricer/fxopt/BlackFxVanillaOptionProductPricer.java) - Prices `ResolvedFxVanillaOption` using Black's formula with lognormal volatilities. Uses `DiscountingFxSingleProductPricer` for underlying FX pricing.\n\n2. **BlackFxVanillaOptionTradePricer** (modules/pricer/src/main/java/com/opengamma/strata/pricer/fxopt/BlackFxVanillaOptionTradePricer.java) - Prices `ResolvedFxVanillaOptionTrade` by combining product pricing and payment discounting using `DiscountingPaymentPricer`.\n\n3. **VannaVolgaFxVanillaOptionProductPricer** (modules/pricer/src/main/java/com/opengamma/strata/pricer/fxopt/VannaVolgaFxVanillaOptionProductPricer.java) - Prices `ResolvedFxVanillaOption` using the Vanna-Volga method, which adjusts Black prices for implied volatility smile effects.\n\n4. **VannaVolgaFxVanillaOptionTradePricer** (modules/pricer/src/main/java/com/opengamma/strata/pricer/fxopt/VannaVolgaFxVanillaOptionTradePricer.java) - Prices `ResolvedFxVanillaOptionTrade` using Vanna-Volga method with payment discounting.\n\n### Measure Calculation Layer (modules/measure)\nThe calculation engine layer wires pricers to measure computation:\n\n1. **FxVanillaOptionMethod** (modules/measure/src/main/java/com/opengamma/strata/measure/fxopt/FxVanillaOptionMethod.java) - An enum with values BLACK and VANNA_VOLGA that controls which pricer to use for calculations. Implements `NamedEnum` and `CalculationParameter`.\n\n2. **FxVanillaOptionMeasureCalculations** (modules/measure/src/main/java/com/opengamma/strata/measure/fxopt/FxVanillaOptionMeasureCalculations.java) - Internal multi-scenario measure calculator that holds references to both `BlackFxVanillaOptionTradePricer` and `VannaVolgaFxVanillaOptionTradePricer` and dispatches measure calculations based on method.\n\n3. **FxVanillaOptionTradeCalculations** (modules/measure/src/main/java/com/opengamma/strata/measure/fxopt/FxVanillaOptionTradeCalculations.java) - Public API class for single-scenario calculations on `ResolvedFxVanillaOptionTrade`, wrapping `FxVanillaOptionMeasureCalculations`.\n\n4. **FxVanillaOptionTradeCalculationFunction** (modules/measure/src/main/java/com/opengamma/strata/measure/fxopt/FxVanillaOptionTradeCalculationFunction.java) - Implements `CalculationFunction<FxVanillaOptionTrade>`, integrating with StandardComponents to compute measures for the calculation engine. Resolves trades, retrieves pricers based on `FxVanillaOptionMethod`, and computes required measures.\n\n### Loader Layer (modules/loader)\n**FxVanillaOptionTradeCsvPlugin** (modules/loader/src/main/java/com/opengamma/strata/loader/csv/FxVanillaOptionTradeCsvPlugin.java) - Implements `TradeCsvParserPlugin` and `TradeCsvWriterPlugin<FxVanillaOptionTrade>`, providing CSV serialization/deserialization for FX vanilla option trades. Registered via service providers in META-INF configuration.\n\n### Barrier Option Dependency\n**FxSingleBarrierOption** (modules/product/src/main/java/com/opengamma/strata/product/fxopt/FxSingleBarrierOption.java) - A Joda-Beans class embedding `FxVanillaOption` as the `underlyingOption` field, representing a knock-in or knock-out variant. This demonstrates how `FxVanillaOption` serves as a reusable building block in more complex FX derivatives.\n\n### Summary\nThe FxVanillaOption type family spans 14 core files across 4 modules:\n- **Product module (4 files)**: Domain classes FxVanillaOption, FxVanillaOptionTrade, and their resolved forms, plus FxSingleBarrierOption which depends on FxVanillaOption\n- **Pricer module (4 files)**: Black and Vanna-Volga pricing implementations at both product and trade levels\n- **Measure module (4 files)**: FxVanillaOptionMethod enum, measure calculators, calculation function, and calculation API\n- **Loader module (1 file)**: CSV plugin for trade persistence\n\nThe architecture follows a consistent pattern: unresolved domain → resolved domain → pricing → measure calculation → calculation function → loader, enabling flexible pricing method selection via the method parameter."
